{{Nihongo|'''Ayumu Seko'''|瀬古 歩夢|Seko Ayumu|born 7 June 2000}} is a Japanese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|475585}}</ref>

==Club career==
Seko joined [[Cerezo Osaka]] in 2016. On 13 November, he debuted for their [[Cerezo Osaka U-23|U-23 squad]] in [[J3 League]] (v [[Kataller Toyama]]).<ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFIX04/?player_id=19480 J.League Data Site]</ref><ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFMS02/?match_card_id=18893 Match report J.League Data Site]</ref> He gave his [[J1 League]] debut for the main squad on 7 December 2019, in 2–0 victory over [[Oita Trinita|Ōita]].

He signed a three-year contract with [[Swiss Super League]] team [[Grasshopper Club Zürich]] on 18 January 2022.<ref>[https://www.gcz.ch/news/news/artikel/gc-verpflichtet-innenverteidiger-ayumu-seko/ GC VERPFLICHTET INNENVERTEIDIGER AYUMU SEKO]</ref> On 17 June 2025, it was announced that he would depart Grasshoppers that summer, having made 117 league appearances for the Swiss record champions.<ref name="departures">{{cite web |title=GC Zürich verabschiedet mehrere Spieler |url=https://www.gcz.ch/news/artikel/1/gc-zuerich-verabschiedet-mehrere-spieler/ |publisher=[[Grasshopper Club Zurich]] |access-date=17 June 2025 |date=17 June 2025}}</ref>

On 23 July 2025, he signed with [[Ligue 1]] side [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ayumu Seko débarque au HAC ! |url=https://www.hac-foot.com/actualite/ayumu-seko-debarque-au-hac.html |publisher=[[Le Havre AC]] |access-date=23 July 2025 |language=fr |date=23 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Seko was called up to give his debut for the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]] in a friendly against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] on 21 January 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20211207/p2g/00m/0sp/060000c |title=Soccer: Japan name J-League based 22-man squad for Jan. Uzbekistan friendly |access-date=2022-01-18 |archive-date=2022-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118102706/https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20211207/p2g/00m/0sp/060000c |url-status=dead }}</ref> However, the match was cancelled by the [[Japan Football Association|JFA]] due to COVID restrictions.<ref>[http://www.tashkenttimes.uz/sports/8138-japan-football-association-cancels-friendly-against-uzbekistan-due-to-covid-restrictions  Japan Football Association cancels friendly against Uzbekistan due to COVID restrictions]</ref>

In March 2023, he was called up by [[Hajime Moriyasu]] for friendlies against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] and [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]]. This time, he was able to make his debut, having played a full match against Uruguay on 24 March 2023, which ended in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/665808|title=Substitute Nishimura strikes to earn Japan draw against Uruguay|access-date=24 March 2023|date=24 March 2023|author=Michael Church|publisher=ESPN|website=espn.co.uk|language=en-uk}}</ref>

